				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This should go without saying, but NES audio (except the 163 and VRC7) is unipolar. All sounds, including ultrasonic, have a DC component. The triangle halts instead of being silenced to zero, but any other channel, when set to an ultrasonic period, will produce audible clicks on every volume change.<br /><br />If that's what Mesen is doing, it's 100% correct.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

