				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The logic used for the scroll position is pretty much identical to what visual studio does: if the next instruction isn't visible in the current view, scroll the view so that the line containing the instruction is in the center of it. Otherwise, don't scroll at all.  This typically means that it won't scroll until you reach the bottom of the window, and then scroll back to the center of it (except when dealing with jumps/etc). I'm not completely certain whether this is what you're getting or not based on your description, though.<br /><br />Either way, I could easily add an option to always scroll the current instruction to the middle of the viewport, if that works better for you?</div>

